has the benefit of easier to do a workout because as a tool to replace the existing gym equipment in the gym place.";i:32;s:155:"While intense exercise is not always recommended for the elderly exercises that improve flexibility balance strength and cardiovascular health usually are.";i:33;s:137:"Though exercise is good for senior citizens it is smart for seniors to speak with their doctors before starting any new exercise program.";i:34;s:31:"Senior Chair Exercise Pictures.";i:35;s:62:"Chair exercises can help increase circulation and flexibility.";i:36;s:59:"They can also strengthen postural and mobilization muscles.";i:37;s:110:"A chair can be used to stretch safely with less risk of losing your balance and can easily be moved or stored.";i:38;s:58:"You might even try free weights with your chair exercises.";i:39;s:60:"Avoid chairs with arms as these will restrict your movement.";i:40;s:58:"Wear loose comfortable clothing and keep some water handy.";i:41;s:89:"Build up slowly and aim to gradually increase the repetitions of each exercise over time.";i:42;s:104:"Try to do these exercises at least twice a week and combine them with the other routines in this series.";i:43;s:140:"Senior woman doing crossword with grandchildren playing in the background - senior chair exercise stock pictures royalty-free photos images.";i:44;s:153:"Female pilates instructor assisting mature student on high-low chair during class in exercise studio - senior chair exercise stock pictures royalty-free.";i:45;s:44:"Why chair exercises are helpful for seniors.";i:46;s:66:"A major benefit of chair exercises is the reduced risk of falling.";i:47;s:94:"Its also a great way for seniors with limited mobility to get the health benefits of exercise.";i:48;s:119:"Chair exercises can be just as challenging as regular standing workouts especially for upper body or abdominal muscles.";i:49;s:181:"Seated resistance band exercises are a great option for seniors especially if they are confined to a wheelchair or have limited mobility due to arthritis or other health conditions.";i:50;s:95:"Exercising from a seated position will help them build their strength and regain their balance.";i:51;s:38:"The Best Chair Yoga Poses for Seniors.";i:52;s:91:"In the following you can learn to do different chair yoga poses that are great for seniors.";i:53;s:48:"All poses are described carefully with pictures.";i:54;s:40:"Be mindful of your body and your breath.";i:55;s:111:"If you find it hard to breathe in one of the postures slowly back out and choose another variation of the pose.";}}